label.value: cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: An action potential that occurs in a cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: cardiac muscle cell action potential involved in contraction

value.value: An action potential that occurs in a cardiac muscle cell and is involved in its contraction.

label.value: cardiac muscle cell contraction

value.value: The actin filament-based process in which cytoplasmic actin filaments slide past one another resulting in contraction of a cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: regulation of cardiac muscle cell contraction

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle cell contraction.

label.value: ventricular cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: An action potential that occurs in a ventricular cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: voltage-gated sodium channel activity involved in cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: Enables the transmembrane transfer of a sodium ion by a voltage-gated channel through the plasma membrane of a cardiac muscle cell contributing to the depolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

label.value: voltage-gated calcium channel activity involved in cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: Enables the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a voltage-gated channel across the plasma membrane of a cardiac muscle cell that contributes to the depolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

label.value: voltage-gated potassium channel activity involved in cardiac muscle cell action potential repolarization

value.value: Enables the transmembrane transfer of a potassium ion by a voltage-gated channel through the plasma membrane of a cardiac muscle cell contributing to the repolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

label.value: membrane repolarization

value.value: The process in which ions are transported across a membrane such that the membrane potential changes in the repolarizing direction, toward the steady state potential. For example, the repolarization during an action potential is from a positive membrane potential towards a negative resting potential.

label.value: membrane depolarization during action potential

value.value: The process in which membrane potential changes in the depolarizing direction from the negative resting potential towards the positive membrane potential that will be the peak of the action potential.

label.value: membrane repolarization during action potential

value.value: The process in which ions are transported across a membrane such that the membrane potential changes in the direction from the positive membrane potential at the peak of the action potential towards the negative resting potential.

label.value: membrane depolarization during cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: The process in which cardiac muscle cell membrane potential changes in the depolarizing direction from the negative resting potential towards the positive membrane potential that will be the peak of the action potential.

label.value: membrane repolarization during cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: The process in which ions are transported across a membrane such that the cardiac muscle cell plasma membrane potential changes in the direction from the positive membrane potential at the peak of the action potential towards the negative resting potential.

label.value: atrial cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: An action potential that occurs in an atrial cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: SA node cell action potential

value.value: An action potential that occurs in a sinoatrial node cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: AV node cell action potential

value.value: An action potential that occurs in an atrioventricular node cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: Purkinje myocyte action potential

value.value: An action potential that occurs in a Purkinje myocyte.

label.value: SA node cell to atrial cardiac muscle cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from an SA node cardiomyocyte to an atrial cardiomyocyte.

label.value: cell-cell signaling involved in cardiac conduction

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another and contributes to the heart process that regulates cardiac muscle contraction; beginning with the generation of an action potential in the sinoatrial node and ending with regulation of contraction of the myocardium.

label.value: gap junction channel activity involved in SA node cell-atrial cardiac muscle cell electrical coupling

value.value: A wide pore channel activity that enables a direct cytoplasmic connection from an SA node cell to an atrial cardiomyocyte. The gap junction passes electrical signals between the cells contributing to cardiac conduction.

label.value: SA node cell to atrial cardiac muscle cell communication by electrical coupling

value.value: The process that mediates signaling interactions between an SA node cardiomyocyte and an atrial cardiomyocyte by transfer of current between their adjacent cytoplasms via intercellular protein channels.

label.value: SA node cell-atrial cardiac muscle cell adhesion involved in cell communication

value.value: The attachment of SA node cardiomyocyte to an atrial cardiomyocyte via adhesion molecules that results in the cells being juxtaposed so that they can communicate.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-activating adrenergic receptor signaling pathway involved in heart process

value.value: The series of molecular signals beginning with a G protein-coupled adrenergic cell surface receptor combining with epinephrine or norepinephrine, to activate adenylate cyclase, which contributes to a circulatory system process carried out by the heart.

label.value: atrial cardiac muscle cell to AV node cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from an atrial cardiomyocyte to an AV node cell.

label.value: AV node cell to bundle of His cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from an AV node cardiac muscle cell to a bundle of His cardiomyocyte.

label.value: bundle of His cell to Purkinje myocyte signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from a bundle of His cardiomyocyte to a Purkinje myocyte.

label.value: Purkinje myocyte to ventricular cardiac muscle cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from a Purkinje myocyte to a ventricular cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-activating adrenergic receptor signaling pathway involved in cardiac muscle relaxation

value.value: An adrenergic receptor signaling pathway that contributes to a reduction in cardiac muscle contraction. Beta-adrenergic receptor-induced cardiac relaxation is achieved by a GPCR-activated adenylate cyclase generating cAMP; cAMP then activates the cAMP-dependent protein kinase A (PKA), which phosphorylates the sarcoplasmic reticulum (SR) membrane protein PLB. In its non-phosphorylated state, PLB acts as an inhibitor of the ATPase Ca(2+) pump of the cardiac SR (SERCA2a); inhibition of the pump is relieved upon phosphorylation. The pump removes Ca(2+) from the cytoplasm, thereby preventing cytosolic Ca(2+)-dependent activation of contractile proteins, leading to enhanced muscle relaxation.

label.value: G protein-coupled acetylcholine receptor signaling pathway involved in negative regulation of heart rate

value.value: A G protein-coupled acetylcholine receptor signaling pathway that contributes to a decrease in frequency or rate of heart contraction. Binding of acetylcholine to a G protein-coupled (muscarinic) receptor on the surface of the signal-receiving cell results in the alpha subunit of a coupled G-protein binding to GTP. This results in the separation of the beta-gamma complex from the alpha subunit. Both the alpha subunit, and the beta-gamma complex can continue to signal to bring about membrane hyperpolarization and a reduction in heart rate.

label.value: regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

value.value: Any process that modulates the establishment or extent of a membrane potential in a cardiac muscle cell (a cardiomyocyte). A membrane potential is the electric potential existing across any membrane arising from charges in the membrane itself and from the charges present in the media on either side of the membrane.

label.value: P-type sodium:potassium-exchanging transporter activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

value.value: Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: ATP + H2O + Na+(in) + K+(out) = ADP + phosphate + Na+(out) + K+(in), that contributes to regulating the membrane potential of a cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: calcium:sodium antiporter activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

value.value: Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: Ca2+(in) + Na+(out) = Ca2+(out) + Na+(in), which contributes to regulating the membrane potential of a cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: P-type calcium transporter activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

value.value: A calcium-transporting P-type ATPase activity involved in regulation of the plasma membrane potential.

label.value: sodium:proton antiporter activity involved in regulation of cardiac muscle cell membrane potential

value.value: Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a cardiac muscle cell membrane to the other according to the reaction: Na+(out) + H+(in) = Na+(in) + H+(out). This transfer contributes to the regulation of the cardiac muscle cell plasma membrane potential.

label.value: voltage-gated potassium channel activity involved in SA node cell action potential depolarization

value.value: Enables the transmembrane transfer of a potassium ion by a voltage-gated channel through the plasma membrane of an SA node cardiac muscle cell contributing to the depolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.

label.value: cardiac muscle cell-cardiac muscle cell adhesion

value.value: The attachment of one cardiomyocyte to another cardiomyocyte via adhesion molecules.

label.value: bundle of His cell action potential

value.value: An action potential that occurs in a bundle of His cell.

label.value: atrial cardiac muscle cell to AV node cell communication by electrical coupling

value.value: The process that mediates signaling interactions between an atrial cardiomyocyte and an AV node cell by transfer of current between their adjacent cytoplasms via intercellular protein channels.

label.value: membrane depolarization during AV node cell action potential

value.value: The process in which AV node cardiac muscle cell membrane potential changes in the depolarizing direction from the negative resting potential towards the positive membrane potential that will be the peak of the action potential.

label.value: membrane depolarization during SA node cell action potential

value.value: The process in which SA node cardiac muscle cell membrane potential changes in the depolarizing direction from the negative resting potential towards the positive membrane potential that will be the peak of the action potential.

label.value: membrane depolarization during Purkinje myocyte cell action potential

value.value: The process in which Purkinje myocyte membrane potential changes in the depolarizing direction from the negative resting potential towards the positive membrane potential that will be the peak of the action potential.

label.value: membrane depolarization during bundle of His cell action potential

value.value: The process in which bundle of His cardiac muscle cell membrane potential changes in the depolarizing direction from the negative resting potential towards the positive membrane potential that will be the peak of the action potential.

label.value: membrane repolarization during AV node cell action potential

value.value: The process in which ions are transported across a membrane such that the AV node cardiac muscle cell membrane potential changes in the direction from the positive membrane potential at the peak of the action potential towards the negative resting potential.

label.value: membrane repolarization during bundle of His cell action potential

value.value: The process in which ions are transported across a membrane such that the bundle of His cardiac muscle cell membrane potential changes in the direction from the positive membrane potential at the peak of the action potential towards the negative resting potential.

label.value: membrane repolarization during Purkinje myocyte action potential

value.value: The process in which ions are transported across a membrane such that the Purkinje myocyte membrane potential changes in the direction from the positive membrane potential at the peak of the action potential towards the negative resting potential.

label.value: membrane repolarization during SA node cell action potential

value.value: The process in which an SA node cardiac muscle cell membrane potential changes in the direction from the positive membrane potential at the peak of the action potential towards the negative resting potential.

label.value: AV node cell to bundle of His cell communication by electrical coupling

value.value: The process that mediates signaling interactions between an AV node cardiomyocyte and a bundle of His cardiac muscle cell by transfer of current between their adjacent cytoplasms via intercellular protein channels.

label.value: bundle of His cell to Purkinje myocyte communication by electrical coupling

value.value: The process that mediates signaling interactions between a bundle of His cardiac muscle cell and a Purkinje myocyte by transfer of current between their adjacent cytoplasms via intercellular protein channels.

label.value: Purkinje myocyte to ventricular cardiac muscle cell communication by electrical coupling

value.value: The process that mediates signaling interactions between a Purkinje myocyte and a ventricular cardiac muscle cell by transfer of current between their adjacent cytoplasms via intercellular protein channels.

label.value: voltage-gated calcium channel activity involved in AV node cell action potential

value.value: Enables the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a voltage-gated channel across the plasma membrane of an AV node cardiac muscle cell that contributes to the depolarization phase of an action potential. A voltage-gated channel is a channel whose open state is dependent on the voltage across the membrane in which it is embedded.
